result.execSummary:
The defendant Keuane Omarr Gilbert was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Total fine and costs in the amount of $642 to be paid by payment plan at a rate of $40 per month commencing March 1st, 2017 and to be paid on the first of each month thereafter.  Failure to pay will result in one day jail for each $25 owed for contempt of court.
Defendant to submit a DNA sample.
